Allow gorilla to run with TCL 8.6

Allow gorilla to run with TCL 8.6

Remove hardcoded version of tclsh. This prevented gorilla to run on
OSes with a version of TCL more recent than 8.5 (for instance Fedora
23 is shipped with TCL 8.6). By not specigfying the version of TCL
called, gorilla runs correctly with TCL 8.6.

Fix file permissions on non-executable types

Only tcl/shell scripts with an actual entry point should have
executable permissions set.

This avoids extra steps during packaging to fix those
permissions.

Disable Look for update if downloads.txt not found

Packaged versions of the software shouldn't contain this
file, which will disable the option altogether.
